# Array Right Rotation in C

This program performs right rotation of an array by k positions using C language.

While solving this problem, I explored different ways of rotating arrays and understood how array shifting works internally.

## Concepts Practiced
- Arrays
- Traversal
- Indexing
- Rotation Logic
- Modulo Operator
- Auxiliary Space

## Problems I Faced
- Initially, I did not handle the case when k > n.
- I realized that directly using large k values can create invalid indexes.
- I also understood why full rotations return the same array.

## Important Realizations
- k % n helps reduce unnecessary rotations.
- Arrays behave cyclically during rotations.
- Manual shifting logic improved my understanding more than directly using optimized code.

## What I Learned
- Array manipulation
- Edge case handling
- Debugging logic errors
- Importance of dry runs before coding
- Difference between working code and optimized code

